data.title: Jump Crypto exchanges $205M in Solana for Bitcoin, leading to a drop in SOL's price amid market fluctuations.
data.description: The exchange of $205 million worth of Solana into Bitcoin by Jump Crypto has led to a notable decrease in SOL's price, mirroring wider market patterns.

data.title: Bluesky Digital Assets shares corporate updates, releases corrective disclosure.
data.description: A recent report reveals that the unemployment rate in the United States has dropped to 4.2%, the lowest it has been in over 50 years. The country added 531,000 jobs in October, exceeding economists' expectations. This improvement in the job market has been attributed to the reopening of businesses and increasing consumer demand. The leisure and hospitality sector saw the most significant growth, adding 164,000 jobs. Additionally, average hourly earnings rose by 0.4% in October. These positive trends indicate a recovering economy and offer hope for many Americans during these challenging times.

data.title: 1.5M Angelenos still at risk despite judicial rulings. Urgent action needed for SNAP benefit suspension. CEO calls for solutions.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, Miguel Santana, the president and CEO of the California Community Foundation (CCF), emphasized the critical importance of addressing food insecurity as the possible suspension of SNAP benefits looms. Santana stressed the necessity for prompt relief measures and long-term solutions to combat this issue.

data.title: COMPUCHILD expands to Castro Valley and San Leandro, California with new franchisee, offering STEAM-focused education programs.
data.description: A new franchisee has recently joined the COMPUCHILD Children's Education franchise family based in DUBLIN, Calif. The announcement was made on October 31, 2025. COMPUCHILD is known for offering Entrepreneurial STEAM™-focused after-school education programs catering to children. This addition marks a significant expansion for the franchise, showcasing its commitment to providing quality education to children.

data.title: Philanthropist Patrick Carroll commits to Boys & Girls Clubs of Greater Tampa Bay with a substantial five-year investment.Total Amount: undisclosedDuration: 5 yearsFocus Area: Health & Wellness ProgramDate: Oct. 31, 2025
data.description: In Tampa Bay, Florida on October 31, 2025, Patrick Carroll, an entrepreneur and philanthropist, disclosed a significant pledge for the Boys & Girls Clubs of Greater Tampa Bay. The commitment spans five years and emphasizes bolstering the organization's Health & Wellness Program aimed at aiding youth mental health.

data.title: VERZUZ returns at COMPLEXCON with Cash Money vs. No Limit Records. Over 8.4M viewers streamed live on Apple Music.
data.description: The VERZUZ event, featuring a showdown between Cash Money Records and No Limit, was livestreamed on Apple Music and attracted over 8.4 million viewers. The event took place on Saturday, October 25, 2025, at ComplexCon in Los Angeles.

data.title: Founder of Intuition warns against AI training on subpar data, stressing dangers of recursive learning. Billy Luedtke addresses key concerns.
data.description: Billy Luedtke from Intuition has raised concerns regarding AI models being trained on inadequate data quality. He has underlined the risks associated with recursive AI learning. The dangers of relying on subpar data for training AI models have been emphasized, pointing towards the potential issues that may arise from this practice.

data.title: ThreeD Capital Inc. and Park Place Limited acquired 5,000,000 units of infinitii ai inc., increasing ownership by >2%.
data.description: Canadian venture capital firm ThreeD Capital Inc. announced the acquisition of unsecured convertible debentures of infinitii ai inc. in October 2025, resulting in ownership of 5,000,000 units of the Company. Each unit includes one common share and one warrant for the purchase of another common share. This acquisition increased ThreeD and Joint Actor's ownership by more than 2% on a partially diluted basis compared to previous reports.

data.title: Lombard Finance buys $538M BTC.b infrastructure from Avalanche, aiming to expand to Ethereum, Solana by 2025.
data.description: Lombard Finance has completed the acquisition of a significant infrastructure asset valued at $538 million known as BTC.b from Avalanche. The company has outlined its strategic growth plans, aiming to expand its operations to include Ethereum, Solana, and other prominent blockchain networks by the year 2025. This move signifies Lombard Finance's commitment to diversifying its portfolio and establishing a strong presence across various blockchain ecosystems in the coming years.

data.title: Humanoid Global partners with Gold Standard Media for advertising, $400,000 for 12 months, can be terminated, contact CEO for info.
data.description: Vancouver, British Columbia on October 31, 2025 – Humanoid Global Holdings Corp. (“Humanoid Global” or “the Company”), which trades publicly as CSE:ROBO, FWB:0XM1, OTCQB:RBOHF, has signed an Advertising Agreement with Gold Standard Media, LLC (“GSM”). The deal includes services like landing pages, digital marketing, email marketing, and influencer marketing. This 12-month agreement kicks off on October 31, 2025, requiring the Company to compensate GSM a total of US$400,000. Both parties hold the right to terminate the contract at any point. GSM's business address is 723 W University Avenue, Georgetown, TX 78626, with CEO Kenneth Ameduri reachable at +1 512-843-1723 or ceo@goldstandardir.com. The relationship between GSM and the Company’s principals is at arm’s length.

data.title: NETGEAR granted equity awards to new employees under Nasdaq rule 5635(c)(4); used inducement plan for non-employees.
data.description: In San Jose, California, NETGEAR, Inc. (Nasdaq: NTGR), a leading provider of intelligent networking solutions, revealed granting inducement equity awards to new staff who have recently joined the company. This initiative aims at providing equity awards to individuals who were not part of NETGEAR's workforce before or who returned to the company after a genuine period of non-employment as an incentive for joining.

data.title: Quantum BioPharma Ltd. announces an at-the-market offering of Class B shares up to $21,225,000 with a 3.0% commission to sales agent Wainwright.
data.description: Quantum BioPharma Ltd. (NASDAQ: QNTM) (CSE: QNTM) (FRA: 0K9A) announced today its initiation of an at-the-market offering agreement with H.C. Wainwright & Co., LLC. The agreement, effective as of February 16, 2024, allows Quantum to offer and sell Class B Subordinate Voting Shares totaling up to US$21,225,000 through Wainwright as the sales agent. It is noted that a cash commission of 3.0% will be paid to Wainwright based on the total gross proceeds attained through the ATM Offering. Quantum, a biopharmaceutical company focused on innovative assets and biotech solutions, is enthusiastic about this opportunity for financial growth.

data.title: Sei (SEI) price drops 7% post Robinhood listing, amid broader market downturn and bearish technical signals.
data.description: The value of Sei (SEI) token has dropped by more than 7% after being listed on Robinhood, as the overall cryptocurrency market faces a downturn. Technical indicators are pointing towards additional decreases in value.

data.title: NASA secures Moon lander backups from SpaceX & Blue Origin amid China's rising lunar ambitions; Elon Musk faces criticism.
data.description: NASA is concerned about China potentially winning the upcoming moon race. Meanwhile, Elon Musk and his company faced criticism from detractors.

data.title: Nordea plans to introduce Bitcoin synthetic ETPs in December 2025, aligning with European crypto regulations.
data.description: Starting in December 2025, Nordea plans to introduce synthetic ETPs linked to Bitcoin, representing a notable advancement in crypto acceptance within Europe under the MiCA regulations.

data.title: Fed Chair Powell hints at possible rate cuts, sparking S&P 500 rally; odds of cut in Sept fall to around 70%.
data.description: There is still anticipation in the markets for a rate reduction next month, although the likelihood has decreased to approximately 70%. Following remarks from Fed Chair Powell indicating that current conditions "may warrant" rate cuts, the S&P 500 experienced a surge, reacting positively to his speech at Jackson Hole.

data.title: High PPI inflation dashes hopes for big Fed rate cut; Trump administration calls for half-point cut next month. S&P 500 drops.
data.description: The Trump administration is advocating for a 0.5% reduction in interest rates in the upcoming month. However, hopes for a significant rate cut by the Federal Reserve were dampened by higher than expected Producer Price Index (PPI) inflation figures. Consequently, the S&P 500 index experienced a decline in response to these developments.

data.title: Core CPI inflation surpasses 3%, won't halt Fed; S&P 500 increases. Fed rate cuts remain unaffected.
data.description: The latest data reveals a significant increase in the core CPI inflation rate, surpassing 3%. Despite this rise, it is not substantial enough to prevent the Federal Reserve from implementing rate cuts. Concurrently, the S&P 500 experienced growth following the announcement.

data.title: Job cuts increased by 140% in July compared to a year ago. The Fed's preferred inflation measure exceeded expectations. S&P 500 rose.
data.description: Recent data reveals a significant increase in job cuts, with a 140% rise compared to the previous year in July. Additionally, the Federal Reserve's preferred inflation measure exceeded expectations. This news comes as the S&P 500 index saw a positive trend, climbing higher.

data.title: Dow Jones Futures: Nvidia, Microsoft, Palantir, Tesla all in buy zones after market rally on Monday.
data.description: On Monday, Dow Jones Futures revealed that Nvidia, Microsoft, Palantir, and Tesla were situated in buy zones following a surge in the stock market. This news comes after a significant market rally. This information is valuable for investors looking to capitalize on potential opportunities in the market.
